****** Definition ****** 

Python is an Open source, Free, High-level, Dynamic, and Interpreted programming language. Python was released in 1991 by Guido van Rossum. Python programing language is one of the cleanest and easy to learn a language in the programming world. It’s easy syntax improved the readability of the code and makes it easy to understand.

****** History of Python *******

History of Python starts in the late 1980s at Centrum Wiskunde and Informatica, Python language was Designed by Guido Van Rossum and was first released in 1991. Python language is the successor of ABC Language which had the feature of exception handling. Guido Van Rossum worked on the creation of ABC and so he took the syntax and features of the language, then solved all the issues with the language and created a good scripting language.

****** Features Of Python ******

1. Easy to Learn and Read
Python has simple and clear syntax, so beginners can learn it quickly.
Its code looks almost like normal English, which makes it easy to understand.

2. Free and Open Source
Python is completely free to use.
Anyone can download it, use it, and even improve it because its source code is publicly available.

3. Object-Oriented Language
Python supports Object-Oriented Programming (OOP).
This helps programmers organize code using classes and objects, making large projects easier to manage.

4. Portable Language
Python programs can run on different operating systems like Windows, Linux, and Mac with very few changes.
This means the same code can work on many computers.

5. Large Library Support
Python provides many built-in libraries and tools.
These libraries help in web development, data science, AI, games, automation, and many other tasks without writing everything from scratch.

6. Interpreted Language
Python executes code line by line using an interpreter.
This makes debugging easier because errors can be found quickly during execution.


****** Advantages of Python ****** 
1. Easy to learn
2. Simple and readable syntax
3. Less coding required
4. Large libraries available
5. Works on multiple platforms
6. Fast development

****** Disadvantages of Python ****** 
1. Slower execution speed
2. Uses more memory
3. Not ideal for mobile apps
4. Runtime errors possible
5. Weak for high-performance tasks
6. Less suitable for game development

****** Steps to Install Python on Windows ****** 
1. Open the official website:
2. Python Downloads
3. Click Download Python.
4. Run the downloaded .exe file.
5. ✔️ Tick “Add Python to PATH”.
6. Click Install Now.
7. Wait for installation to finish.
8. Click Close.
     Verify installation:
     Open Command Prompt

Type:
python --version
If version appears, Python is installed successfully.

